00:11:28,762 --> 00:11:30,929
(sighing)

254
00:11:30,930 --> 00:11:31,930
(squealing)
ah!

255
00:11:31,931 --> 00:11:33,432
That was perfectly measured!

256
00:11:33,433 --> 00:11:34,933
(squealing, laughing)

257
00:11:34,934 --> 00:11:36,035
There you go!

258
00:11:36,036 --> 00:11:38,137
(laughter)

259
00:11:45,578 --> 00:11:46,745
What the hell?

260
00:11:48,415 --> 00:11:50,549
(chuckles)
(sighing)

261
00:11:50,550 --> 00:11:52,918
We're baking.

262
00:11:52,919 --> 00:11:55,054
I can see that.

263
00:11:55,055 --> 00:11:57,523
I'm gonna go change.

264
00:12:03,229 --> 00:12:05,564
Where's my jelly creme center?

265
00:12:05,565 --> 00:12:08,267
Sorry, dad, I must've forgotten.

266
00:12:08,268 --> 00:12:10,002
What's up with your brain today?

267
00:12:10,003 --> 00:12:11,503
You know,
I think it's going soft

268
00:12:11,504 --> 00:12:13,372
From all that crap
you put in your hair.

269
00:12:13,373 --> 00:12:16,375
It's organic and I'm fine.

270
00:12:18,478 --> 00:12:21,380
I'm sorry,
it's a glee club thing.

271
00:12:21,381 --> 00:12:23,082
It's not about a guy, is it?

272
00:12:23,083 --> 00:12:25,784
'cause I'm not ready
to have that conversation.

273
00:12:25,785 --> 00:12:27,653
Oh, at least you don't
have to worry about me

274
00:12:27,654 --> 00:12:29,421
Getting someone pregnant.
(chuckling)

275
00:12:31,224 --> 00:12:33,392
It's not a guy.

276
00:12:33,393 --> 00:12:35,894
We're doing this amazing song
for sectionals,

277
00:12:35,895 --> 00:12:36,863
A personal favorite of mine,

278
00:12:37,364 --> 00:12:39,632
And Mr. Schuester won't
give me a chance to sing it.

279
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:41,000
Why?

280
00:12:41,001 --> 00:12:43,502
It's traditionally
sung by a girl.

281
00:12:43,503 --> 00:12:45,171
Well, you sing like a girl.

282
00:12:45,172 --> 00:12:46,572
You know, in a good way.

283
00:12:46,573 --> 00:12:48,341
Look, Kurt, I don't know

284
00:12:48,342 --> 00:12:49,909
How this music stuff works.

285
00:12:49,910 --> 00:12:52,411
I'm pretty exclusively committed
to my mellencamp collection

286
00:12:52,412 --> 00:12:55,982
But isn't there more
crossover nowadays?

287
00:12:55,983 --> 00:12:57,650
You know,
chicks doing construction,

288
00:12:57,651 --> 00:12:59,785
Guys wearing dress shoes
with no socks?

289
00:13:01,188 --> 00:13:02,688
Didn't that girl
from your high school

290
00:13:02,689 --> 00:13:04,657
Just join the boy's
wrestling team?

291
00:13:04,658 --> 00:13:05,858
(whistle blowing)
yes!

292
00:13:05,859 --> 00:13:07,159
Whoo!

293
00:13:08,328 --> 00:13:11,897
Yes, but her parents
had to Sue the school.

294
00:13:13,934 --> 00:13:16,535
This is really getting
you down, isn't it?

295
00:13:16,536 --> 00:13:18,871
I'm full of ennui.

296
00:13:18,872 --> 00:13:22,808
<i>So, it's really
getting you down?</i>

297
00:13:25,012 --> 00:13:26,979
Yes.

298
00:13:26,980 --> 00:13:29,715
You can't discriminate against
my kid because of his sex,

299
00:13:29,716 --> 00:13:32,118
Religion,
political affiliation

300
00:13:32,119 --> 00:13:34,220
Or the fact that he's queer
as a three dollar bill.

301
00:13:34,221 --> 00:13:35,287
And I won't accept it.

302
00:13:35,288 --> 00:13:36,622
This isn't academics

303
00:13:36,623 --> 00:13:37,990
Or athletics, Mr. Hummel.

304
00:13:37,991 --> 00:13:40,192
It's an arts program
and Mr. Schuester's

305
00:13:40,193 --> 00:13:42,662
Judgments are subjective.

306
00:13:42,663 --> 00:13:45,031
You put on a blindfold
and listen to my kid sing,

307
00:13:45,032 --> 00:13:46,866
And you will swear you're
hearing Ronnie Spector.

308
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:49,535
Wait.
Don't try to backpedal
on this, Schuester.

309
00:13:49,536 --> 00:13:51,837
I was just going
to agree with you.

310
00:13:51,838 --> 00:13:54,206
I know this is going
to be hard on you, Rachel,

311
00:13:54,207 --> 00:13:55,708
But I can't,
in good conscience,

312
00:13:55,709 --> 00:13:57,677
Preach about the importance
of helping Artie

313
00:13:57,678 --> 00:13:59,645
And then reject Kurt's request
out of hand.

314
00:13:59,646 --> 00:14:01,514
So, you're giving him my part?

315
00:14:01,515 --> 00:14:03,416
Now, I can't just
give him the part.

316
00:14:03,417 --> 00:14:06,085
That would be just as wrong,
but I can let him audition.

317
00:14:06,086 --> 00:14:08,621
What do you mean,
like a tryout?

318
00:14:08,622 --> 00:14:10,256
All right, that seems fair.

319
00:14:10,257 --> 00:14:13,159
This is totally unfair.
You gave me the part.

320
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:15,161
And I will give it to you again

321
00:14:15,162 --> 00:14:17,763
If you can sing the song
better than Kurt.

322
00:14:17,764 --> 00:14:20,199
Okay, this seems
like a reasonable deal.

323
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:22,902
But how do I know this
isn't just some show

324
00:14:22,903 --> 00:14:24,370
To stop me from
taking a flamethrower

325
00:14:24,371 --> 00:14:25,571
To this place?

326
00:14:26,773 --> 00:14:28,674
Who's going to judge?

327
00:14:28,675 --> 00:14:30,710
Now, all of you
are going to judge,

328
00:14:30,711 --> 00:14:32,611
And in the spirit
of full access,

329
00:14:32,612 --> 00:14:34,580
Each of you
is going to get a vote.

330
00:14:34,581 --> 00:14:37,049
Whatever singer
has the most votes,

331
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:39,051
Gets the part.

332
00:14:39,052 --> 00:14:40,586
This isn't going to be
about talent, Mr. Schuester.

333
00:14:40,587 --> 00:14:42,354
It's going to be
a popularity contest.

334
00:14:42,355 --> 00:14:44,256
Stop right there.
Mr. Shue, if I may.

335
00:14:50,530 --> 00:14:53,065
We all know
I'm more popular than Rachel.

336
00:14:53,066 --> 00:14:55,101
And I dress better than her.

337
00:14:55,102 --> 00:14:57,169
But I want you all
to promise me that you're

338
00:14:57,170 --> 00:14:59,071
Going to vote for whoever
sings the song better.

339
00:14:59,072 --> 00:15:01,774
Raise your right hand.

340
00:15:01,775 --> 00:15:03,976
<i>Your right hand, brittany.</i>

341
00:15:03,977 --> 00:15:06,378
It's this one.
Sorry.

342
00:15:06,379 --> 00:15:07,713
Repeat after me.

343
00:15:07,714 --> 00:15:09,882
I promise to vote for
whoever sings the song better.

344
00:15:09,883 --> 00:15:14,253
All:
I promise to vote for
whoever sings the song better.

345
00:15:17,924 --> 00:15:19,291
It's on.

346
00:15:19,292 --> 00:15:21,227
(bell ringing)

347
00:15:22,729 --> 00:15:23,863
All right, guys.

348
00:15:30,403 --> 00:15:32,238
Maybe one of these days
you'll find a way to create

349
00:15:32,239 --> 00:15:34,774
Teaching moments
without ruining my life.

350
00:15:34,775 --> 00:15:39,411
(gentle piano melody plays)

351
00:15:39,412 --> 00:15:41,547
(discordant notes play)

352
00:15:42,075 --> 00:15:45,365
Shue, I saw all your kids
in wheelchairs

353
00:15:45,435 --> 00:15:47,469
And I was very impressed.

354
00:15:47,195 --> 00:15:49,196
Well, thank you,
principal Figgins,

355
00:15:49,272 --> 00:15:51,173
But actually, it's made me
realize that there's only

356
00:15:51,174 --> 00:15:53,075
One wheelchair entrance
in this school

357
00:15:53,076 --> 00:15:55,144
And it's all the way on
the far end of campus.

358
00:15:55,145 --> 00:15:56,501
Mckinley needs ramps.

359
00:15:56,502 --> 00:15:58,702
No way.
Those are what I call

360
00:15:59,498 --> 00:16:00,290
"lazy makers."

361
00:16:00,291 --> 00:16:02,084
They discourage
our able-bodied students

362
00:16:02,085 --> 00:16:04,586
From getting their proper
exercise by using the stairs.

363
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:06,047
What is she doing here?

364
00:16:06,256 --> 00:16:07,258
Yes, what am I doing here?

365
00:16:07,259 --> 00:16:08,526
I have a cheerios routine
to polish

366
00:16:08,559 --> 00:16:09,726
That's gonna
clinch us nationals.

367
00:16:09,727 --> 00:16:11,394
I brought you two in here

368
00:16:11,395 --> 00:16:13,062
Because both of you
have a point.

369
00:16:13,063 --> 00:16:15,131
Handicapped ramps are expensive,

370
00:16:15,132 --> 00:16:19,068
But inspiration is free.

371
00:16:19,069 --> 00:16:21,404
Will, I'm so inspired by
your stunt that I'm insisting

372
00:16:21,405 --> 00:16:23,272
That Ms. Sylvester do
the same with the cheerios.

373
00:16:23,273 --> 00:16:24,807
I beg your pardon?

374
00:16:24,808 --> 00:16:27,243
Cheerios is not accessible, Sue.

375
00:16:27,244 --> 00:16:28,945
It's by invitation only.

376
00:16:28,946 --> 00:16:30,246
I want to see a squad

377
00:16:30,247 --> 00:16:33,349
That reflects
our community's diversity.

378
00:16:33,350 --> 00:16:35,351
Now, glee club
held open auditions.

379
00:16:35,352 --> 00:16:37,120
And everyone got in.

380
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:38,654
Now that Quinn Fabray

381
00:16:38,655 --> 00:16:41,324
Is off the squad,
you will hold open auditions

382
00:16:41,325 --> 00:16:42,458
To fill her slot

383
00:16:42,459 --> 00:16:43,626
And Mr. Schuester

384
00:16:43,627 --> 00:16:45,361
Will monitor them
to make sure

385
00:16:45,362 --> 00:16:46,829
That they are fair to all.

386
00:16:46,830 --> 00:16:48,698
Okay, let me break this
down for you here.

387
00:16:48,699 --> 00:16:50,366
There comes a point

388
00:16:50,367 --> 00:16:52,702
When you've got to stop seeing
people for what they look like,

389
00:16:52,703 --> 00:16:55,004
And ask them to show you
what they can do.

390
00:16:55,005 --> 00:16:57,040
And as soon as
a cheerleader

391
00:16:57,041 --> 00:17:00,243
Rolls herself out onto
the field in a wheelchair,

392
00:17:00,244 --> 00:17:04,013
She becomes decidedly less
effective at cheering people up.

393
00:17:04,014 --> 00:17:05,648
It's just a fact.

394
00:17:05,649 --> 00:17:09,018
No, Sue, the fact is you've
never given other students

395
00:17:09,019 --> 00:17:10,753
The fair shake
that they deserve.

396
00:17:12,122 --> 00:17:13,356
I'm asking you to try it.

397
00:17:13,357 --> 00:17:14,824
What do you have to lose?

398
00:17:14,825 --> 00:17:17,093
Maybe somebody at this school
will surprise you.

399
00:17:19,363 --> 00:17:21,364
Finn:
Cupcake?

400
00:17:23,734 --> 00:17:25,902
These cupcakes suck.
That's why we're
not selling any.

401
00:17:25,903 --> 00:17:28,204
It's not about the cupcakes.
It's about us.

402
00:17:28,205 --> 00:17:30,339
Nobody wants to buy from losers.

403
00:17:30,340 --> 00:17:33,342
We're in glee club
and in wheelchairs.

404
00:17:33,343 --> 00:17:34,610
She has a point.

405
00:17:34,611 --> 00:17:35,845
Six months ago
I could've sold

406
00:17:35,846 --> 00:17:37,513
50 of these things
on fear alone.

407
00:17:39,049 --> 00:17:41,551
Oh, my god.
What is she doing?!

408
00:17:41,552 --> 00:17:44,020
I actually think
they're kind of friends.

409
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:46,522
Brittany is always cheating off
her test papers in math class.

410
00:17:46,523 --> 00:17:49,158
See, so many?

411
00:17:49,159 --> 00:17:50,593
And look how pretty
they are, Becky.

412
00:17:50,594 --> 00:17:52,228
Wow.

413
00:17:52,229 --> 00:17:54,163
Brittany, you're supposed
to be in your wheelchair.

414
00:17:54,164 --> 00:17:55,731
I lost it.

415
00:17:55,732 --> 00:17:57,733
Are you a cheerleader?

416
00:17:57,734 --> 00:17:59,068
It's so cool.

417
00:17:59,069 --> 00:18:00,369
So is buying a cupcake.

418
00:18:00,370 --> 00:18:01,437
That's really cool.

419
00:18:01,438 --> 00:18:03,506
But I don't have any money.

420
00:18:03,507 --> 00:18:05,074
That's okay,
I have some.

421
00:18:13,117 --> 00:18:16,119
Thanks.

422
00:18:16,120 --> 00:18:18,621
So, how much do we have now?

423
00:18:18,622 --> 00:18:22,024
Well, with this one dollar,
we have... One dollar.

424
00:18:22,025 --> 00:18:24,227
This is ridiculous.

425
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:26,195
Well, maybe if we put
a jelly bean or something

426
00:18:26,196 --> 00:18:28,464
On top we'd sell more.
Are you an idiot?!

427
00:18:28,465 --> 00:18:31,200
How am I supposed to trust you
to take care of our baby

428
00:18:31,201 --> 00:18:33,870
When you can't even figure out
how to sell a damn cupcake?

429
00:18:33,871 --> 00:18:35,738
Stop attacking me.
I'm sick of it.

430
00:18:35,739 --> 00:18:36,606
Get a job.

431
00:18:36,607 --> 00:18:37,707
I'm trying!

432
00:18:37,708 --> 00:18:39,876
(chair clattering)

433
00:18:39,877 --> 00:18:40,943
(Quinn scoffs)

434
00:18:40,944 --> 00:18:43,846
(sighs)

435
00:18:48,619 --> 00:18:50,653
Sue:
I don't know what I'm
supposed to be doing here.

436
00:18:50,654 --> 00:18:53,289
You just call a name,
they come in and try out.

437
00:18:53,290 --> 00:18:55,124
Just give them a chance
to express themselves.

438
00:18:55,125 --> 00:18:56,792
I'm about to projectile
express myself

439
00:18:56,793 --> 00:18:58,427
All over your
hush puppies.

440
00:18:58,428 --> 00:19:00,930
Mckinley, hey, hey.

441
00:19:00,931 --> 00:19:03,266
Mckinley, hey, hey.

442
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:04,200
No.

443
00:19:07,504 --> 00:19:09,505
(baton clattering, echoing)

444
00:19:09,506 --> 00:19:10,806
No.

445
00:19:12,309 --> 00:19:13,709
You're not serious, are you?

446
00:19:15,979 --> 00:19:19,148
Tell me you're not serious.

447
00:19:19,149 --> 00:19:19,749
No.

448
00:19:20,751 --> 00:19:22,585
No friggin' way, jacob.

449
00:19:30,427 --> 00:19:32,028
(lightly groaning)

450
00:19:32,029 --> 00:19:33,429
Freak!

451
00:19:35,199 --> 00:19:37,567
Okay, I've been at this for
an hour, that's all I promised.

452
00:19:37,568 --> 00:19:39,735
Sue, there's just one
more person on the list.

453
00:19:39,736 --> 00:19:41,437
Give her a shot.

454
00:19:41,438 --> 00:19:42,905
Becky Johnson!

455
00:19:42,906 --> 00:19:44,473
Jackson.
Jackson.

456
00:19:47,744 --> 00:19:50,012
(sotto voce):
Be nice, Sue.

457
00:19:50,013 --> 00:19:53,082
I heard that you're doing
a routine with jump ropes.

458
00:19:53,083 --> 00:19:55,151
I wanted to show you
what I can do.

459
00:20:07,064 --> 00:20:09,131
Becky, I'm going to stop you
right there.

460
00:20:10,801 --> 00:20:12,501
You're in.

461
00:20:12,502 --> 00:20:14,804
Be at practice tomorrow
at 4:00 p.M.

462
00:20:14,805 --> 00:20:16,105
Congratulations.

463
00:20:20,978 --> 00:20:22,678
What are you up to, sue?

464
00:20:22,679 --> 00:20:24,413
I'm just following orders, Will.

465
00:20:24,414 --> 00:20:25,648
I'm doing what I was told.

466
00:20:25,649 --> 00:20:28,251
And I found myself
a brand-new cheerio.

467
00:20:28,252 --> 00:20:30,886
You're up to something.

468
00:20:30,887 --> 00:20:33,823
I don't like this, sue!

469
00:20:36,827 --> 00:20:39,395
(bell ringing)
I'm just saying,
she has a point.

470
00:20:39,396 --> 00:20:41,163
You are kind
of an idiot.

471
00:20:41,164 --> 00:20:42,465
Nice support, dude.

472
00:20:42,466 --> 00:20:43,933
Whatever happened
to bros before hos?

473
00:20:43,934 --> 00:20:45,568
You've got a baby
on the way, bro.

474
00:20:45,569 --> 00:20:47,103
And you haven't done spit
to take care of it.

475
00:20:47,104 --> 00:20:48,704
Like you'd do
any different?

476
00:20:48,705 --> 00:20:50,072
Damn straight.
How?

477
00:20:50,073 --> 00:20:51,340
Nobody's hiring.

478
00:20:51,341 --> 00:20:53,909
Sell your Xbox,
rob a bank,

479
00:20:53,910 --> 00:20:56,345
Go all Robin Hood on this joint,
whatever it takes.

480
00:20:57,581 --> 00:20:59,448
(wheelchairs cLanging)
all I ever hear is you

481
00:20:59,449 --> 00:21:01,617
Whining and crying
about how hard this is on you.

482
00:21:01,618 --> 00:21:02,718
What about her?

483
00:21:02,719 --> 00:21:04,353
Dude, you are so out of line!

484
00:21:04,354 --> 00:21:05,788
You don't know
what I'm dealing with!

485
00:21:05,789 --> 00:21:07,757
All I know is that you're a punk

486
00:21:07,758 --> 00:21:09,458
Who doesn't deserve to have
Quinn as his girlfriend.

487
00:21:09,459 --> 00:21:11,027
You're a punk!

488
00:21:15,265 --> 00:21:18,367
(grunting, groaning)

489
00:21:22,072 --> 00:21:23,272
Will:
Hey, hey, break it up!

490
00:21:23,273 --> 00:21:24,573
Break it up!

491
00:21:24,574 --> 00:21:26,108
Come on!

492
00:21:26,109 --> 00:21:27,209
Hey!
He started it.

493
00:21:27,210 --> 00:21:28,544
I don't care!

494
00:21:28,545 --> 00:21:29,345
Now...

495
00:21:29,346 --> 00:21:30,446
(sighing)

496
00:21:30,447 --> 00:21:33,082
You-you guys are best friends.

497
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:35,718
What the hell is going on?

498
00:21:35,719 --> 00:21:38,688
I'm just really stressed
about the bake sale.

499
00:21:38,689 --> 00:21:41,023
I really like Artie, okay?

500
00:21:43,360 --> 00:21:45,361
You okay?

501
00:21:49,916 --> 00:21:52,618
The key to a double turn
is to just go for it.

502
00:21:52,619 --> 00:21:55,020
You push with the
right wheel and pull
as hard as you can

503
00:21:55,021 --> 00:21:57,389
With the left, and find a spot
on the wall to spot you,

504
00:21:57,390 --> 00:21:58,424
So you don't get dizzy.

505
00:22:04,898 --> 00:22:07,266
Will:
Okay, guys,
take five, all right?

506
00:22:07,267 --> 00:22:09,935
Oh, remember to show up early
on Thursday.

507
00:22:09,936 --> 00:22:11,403
It's Rachel versus Kurt

508
00:22:11,404 --> 00:22:12,938
For the big solo.

509
00:22:16,476 --> 00:22:17,710
Careful.

510
00:22:17,711 --> 00:22:20,379
Artie:
